h2. Problem Statement
When trying to link JIRA Service Desk Cloud project to a Confluence Cloud that is hosted in a different domain, below error is showing up:
{code}This application link does not support impersonation, by default all requests will be made as an anonymous user. For more information see Application Link.{code}
There is a suggestion ticket [ID-6166|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/ID-6166] to allow the impersonation, but it was closed as _Won't Fix_ since it is working as intended.

h2. Suggestion
It would be great if this limitation is documented somewhere or in [Serving customers with a knowledge base|https://confluence.atlassian.com/servicedeskcloud/serving-customers-with-a-knowledge-base-732528995.html] documentation so that all users are aware of this limitation.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-4921].
  {panel}

h2. Definition

The examples for the *{{pendingBy}}* function in the [Advanced searching|https://confluence.atlassian.com/servicedeskserver033/advanced-searching-functions-reference-861256617.html#Advancedsearching-functionsreference-approvedpendingBy()] is misleading.
h2. Problem

The examples show the JQL queries as:
 * Find issues that require approval by John Smith:
 {{approval = *pending*(jsmith)}}
 * Find issues that require by John Smith or Sarah Khan:
 {{approval = *pending*(jsmith,skhan)}}

h2. Suggestion

The examples should read:
 * Find issues that require approval by John Smith:
 {{approval = *pendingBy*(jsmith)}}
 * Find issues that require by John Smith or Sarah Khan:
 {{approval = *pendingBy*(jsmith,skhan)}}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-4920].
  {panel}

In Service Desk, when creating tickets through email, it will get the *From* address as the reporter for the ticket. However, in some cases, the user might want to use email web forms in order to have the case created. 

 

This is a suggestion to have an option for Jira Service Desk to use the *REPLY-TO* address instead of the *FROM* address in the email header.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Service Desk Cloud*. Using *JIRA Service Desk Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSDSERVER-4917].
  {panel}

h3. Problem Solution:
At the moment, when we run a GET REST API to get a request type details, the response will be shown like below:
{code}GET /rest/servicedeskapi/servicedesk/{serviceDeskId}/requesttype{code}
{code:xml}
{
  "id": "18",
  "_links": {
    "self": "http://xxxxxx/rest/servicedeskapi/servicedesk/1/requesttype/18"
  },
  "name": "Monitor",
  "description": "",
  "helpText": "",
  "serviceDeskId": "1",
  "groupIds": [
    "1"
  ],
  "icon": {
    "id": "10532",
    "_links": {
      "iconUrls": {
        "48x48": "http://xxxxx/secure/viewavatar?avatarType=SD_REQTYPE&size=large&avatarId=10532",
        "24x24": "http://xxxxx/secure/viewavatar?avatarType=SD_REQTYPE&size=small&avatarId=10532",
        "16x16": "http://xxxxx/secure/viewavatar?avatarType=SD_REQTYPE&size=xsmall&avatarId=10532",
        "32x32": "http://xxxxx/secure/viewavatar?avatarType=SD_REQTYPE&size=medium&avatarId=10532"
      }
    }
  }
}
{code}
From here, we could not actually find the key of the request type that is being used for JIRA when storing the Customer Request Type Custom field value in the database.

h3. Suggested Solution:
To include the key in the response or better adding the lowercase project key at the front as how it is in the {{customfieldvalue}} table.

h3. Workaround

See below KB article for a workaround. However, please take into account that this is not supported and it may stop working without any previous notice:
- [How to set the Request Type when creating an issue using Jira Core REST API in Cloud|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/how-to-set-the-request-type-when-creating-an-issue-using-jira-core-rest-api-in-cloud-974366000.html]

